        "timestamp": "2021-06-23 11:32:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(3 comments)\n\nIt seems to me that all validations checks are covered by the 4 following rules:\n\n* restControllerShouldOnlyDependOnRestController\n* apiServiceShouldOnlyDependOnControllerAndServices\n* spiServiceShouldOnlyDependOnControllerAndServices\n* repositoryIsOnlyAccessedByServicesAndRepository\n\nTo simplify the tests, why not keeping only these ones if they are also covering all the others ones ?\n\nAlso, if ever needed, you can give a look to Lang API at https://www.archunit.org/userguide/html/000_Index.html#_the_lang_api to see how to combine predicates and conditions with something like:\n\n  .that().resideInAPackage(\"..service..\")\n  .or().resideInAPackage(\"..persistence..\")\n  .should().accessClassesThat().resideInAPackage(\"..controller..\")\n  .orShould().accessClassesThat().resideInAPackage(\"..ui..\")",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
